    "To implement the matching algorithm in [45], we extract the first five binary bits from each of five randomly selected attributes and concatenate them to form a 25-bit binary string, which serves as the primary key for each tuple.",
    "F.5 Implementation Details for Tabular AttacksWe implement the ten post-processing attacks forTable 3 as below: 1.",
    "removes 10% of rows in a table. 2.",
    "replaces 2 columns with unwatermarked values sampled from the same model. 3.",
    "replaces 10% cells with unwatermarked values sampled from the same model. 4."
  ]
